1. When clicking "Change" in edit mode:
 - The current form state (address type, building name, etc.) is stored
 - Navigation to AddressMap occurs

2. In AddressMap:
 - If coming from edit mode, the map opens centered on the editing address location
 - User can pick a new location
 - When clicking "Enter Full Address", the selected location is stored

3. Back in AddressInfo:
 - The stored form state is restored with the new location
 - All previously entered information is preserved
 - The address display is updated to show the new location

The key improvements are:
- Proper state preservation during the edit flow
- Map centering on the correct location when editing
- Form data persistence when changing locations
- Smooth navigation between the screens

Now when you edit an address and click "Change", it will:
1. Open the map at the current address location
2. Allow you to pick a new location
3. Return to the form with all the previous data intact but with the new location
4. Display the newly selected address while preserving all other fields

This provides a seamless editing experience while maintaining all the user's input data."}]}]}

